# Auto detect text files and perform LF normalization 
* text=auto 

# Ensure Python files use LF line endings for cross-platform compatibility
*.py text eol=lf

# Treat Markdown files as text with LF line endings
*.md text eol=lf

# Handle JSON and YAML files consistently
*.json text eol=lf
*.yml text eol=lf
*.yaml text eol=lf

# Ignore Python cache and compiled files
*.pyc binary
*.pyo binary
__pycache__/ binary

# Treat images as binary files to prevent corruption
*.png binary
*.jpg binary
*.jpeg binary
*.gif binary

# Handle text files properly with UTF-8 encoding
*.txt text encoding=UTF-8

# If you're using a GUI with Tkinter and have font files
*.ttf binary
*.otf binary



ðŸ”¹ Why This is Useful for Your Project
âœ… Python Files (*.py) â†’ Ensures consistent line endings (LF), preventing issues when collaborating across Windows, macOS, and Linux.
âœ… Markdown Files (README.md) â†’ Forces LF line endings for documentation consistency.
âœ… JSON/YAML (*.json, *.yml) â†’ Maintains proper formatting in configuration files.
âœ… Binary Files (*.png, *.jpg, *.pyc) â†’ Prevents Git from modifying images or compiled Python files.
âœ… Text Files (*.txt) â†’ Uses UTF-8 encoding to avoid character corruption in text-based outputs.
âœ… Font Files (*.ttf, *.otf) â†’ If your project has a custom GUI, this ensures font files remain intact.

âœ… Final Steps: Add & Commit the .gitattributes File
Once you've created the .gitattributes file, add and push it to GitHub:

